Mr Kabura was charged before Chief Magistrate Mathias Okuche with an alternative count of committing an indecent act with a minor.
He was also charged with a second count of child sex tourism.
Magistrate Okuche heard that the military officer ferried the minor intending to defile her.
The case will continue on January 19.
He was released on a Sh200,000 bond.
The Kenya Army soldier is said to have committed the heinous act in Kiriaini market, Nyeri County.
A police statement said the soldier volunteered to drop the 16-year-old girl in her school.



