“The suspect abruptly made a stop-over at Kiriaini market where he booked into a room at around mid-day and allegedly defiled the schoolgirl. After the ordeal, he bundled the girl into the car and sped off towards her school,” the statement said in part.
School reporting time
The girl was rescued following an accident that occurred on the Nyeri-Mweiga highway at around 6pm, way past the school reporting time.
Police escorted the girl to the Nyeri County Referral Hospital for examination while the soldier was detained at the Nyeri Police Station.
The latest incident comes just a month after a police officer at Clay City police post allegedly raped a woman he had arrested and detained at the post.



