According to the victim, she was on her way home way past curfew time when the officer, identified as Constable Wilson Waruta, arrested her and took her to the police post along Thika Road.
At the time, Mr Waruta was the only officer that night, and he found the woman alone in a spot notorious for petty crimes at around 2am.
The woman was the only detainee of the night at the police post. Mr Waruta allegedly raped and sodomised the woman at the station before releasing her in the dead of the night.
He then walked out of the police post shortly afterwards and has not been seen or heard from since.
The woman reported the incident at Kasarani Police Station the following day, and officers immediately started investigations.
